[5.437, "o", "\r\n🤖 [@trinity]\r\nAlright, I understand the objective. You want a `render.sh` bash script to combine an image and an audio file into a 5-second MP4 video using FFmpeg, and then execute it. I will follow the Trinity Orchestration Protocol.\r\n\r\n**Phase 1: Pre-Flight Discovery** is complete. I've noted the requirements and confirmed FFmpeg is the tool for the job.\r\n\r\nNow, let's move to **Phase 2: Architect Planning**. I am delegating to `@architect` to design the technical approach for this task.\r\n\r\n@architect, please create a bash script named `render.sh`. This script should use FFmpeg to:\r\n- Take the input image: `/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.png`\r\n- Take the input audio: `/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.wav`\r\n- Generate an MP4 video with a duration of exactly 5 seconds.\r\n- The output video should be named `trinity-demo-output.mp4`.\r\n\r\nPlease provide the exact FFmpeg command to achieve this within the `render.sh` script, ensuring "]
[0.000, "o", "it's suitable for YouTube upload compatibility (e.g., `yuv420p` pixel format). The script should also make sure the output file is in the current working directory.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "[System] Handoff to @architect detected.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "Thinking (@architect)...\r\n"]
[9.239, "o", "\r\n🤖 [@architect]\r\nAlright, @trinity, I have analyzed the requirements for generating the MP4 video. As the Architect, I have designed the `render.sh` script and the specific FFmpeg command to achieve the desired outcome.\r\n\r\n**Architectural Plan:**\r\n\r\n1.  **Script Name:** `render.sh`\r\n2.  **Input Files (Absolute Paths):**\r\n    *   Image: `/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.png`\r\n    *   Audio: `/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.wav`\r\n3.  **Output File (Relative Path):** `./trinity-demo-output.mp4` (will be created in the current working directory where `render.sh` is executed)\r\n4.  **Duration:** Exactly 5 seconds.\r\n5.  **FFmpeg Command Strategy:**\r\n    *   Use `-loop 1` for the image input to ensure it's continuously present for the video's duration.\r\n    *   Specify the audio input.\r\n    *   Set the output duration to `5` seconds using `-t 5`. This ensures the video is exactly 5 seconds long, truncating the audio if it's longer or pad"]
[0.000, "o", "ding with silence if it's shorter.\r\n    *   Use `libx264` for video encoding, `aac` for audio encoding.\r\n    *   Set `tune stillimage` for better quality when the video source is a static image.\r\n    *   Specify `yuv420p` pixel format for broad YouTube compatibility.\r\n    *   A reasonable audio bitrate (`-b:a 192k`) will be applied.\r\n\r\nHere is the `render.sh` script for the @coder to implement:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n#!/bin/bash -e\r\n\r\n# Define input and output files\r\nINPUT_IMAGE=\"/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.png\"\r\nINPUT_AUDIO=\"/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.wav\"\r\nOUTPUT_VIDEO=\"trinity-demo-output.mp4\"\r\nVIDEO_DURATION=\"5\"\r\n\r\necho \"Starting video generation...\"\r\necho \"  Input Image: ${INPUT_IMAGE}\"\r\necho \"  Input Audio: ${INPUT_AUDIO}\"\r\necho \"  Output Video: ${OUTPUT_VIDEO}\"\r\necho \"  Duration: ${VIDEO_DURATION} seconds\"\r\n\r\n# Check if FFmpeg is installed\r\nif ! command -v ffmpeg &> /dev/null\r\nthen\r\n    echo \"Error: FFmpeg is not installed. Ple"]
[0.001, "o", "ase install it to proceed.\"\r\n    exit 1\r\nfi\r\n\r\n# Check if input files exist\r\nif [ ! -f \"${INPUT_IMAGE}\" ]; then\r\n    echo \"Error: Input image file not found at ${INPUT_IMAGE}\"\r\n    exit 1\r\nfi\r\n\r\nif [ ! -f \"${INPUT_AUDIO}\" ]; then\r\n    echo \"Error: Input audio file not found at ${INPUT_AUDIO}\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n# FFmpeg command to combine the image and audio into a 5-second MP4 video\r\n# -loop 1: Loop the image indefinitely\r\n# -i: Specify input files\r\n# -t 5: Set the output duration to exactly 5 seconds\r\n# -c:v libx264: Use H.264 video codec\r\n# -tune stillimage: Optimize for still images\r\n# -pix_fmt yuv420p: Set pixel format for YouTube compatibility\r\n# -c:a aac: Use AAC audio codec\r\n# -b:a 192k: Set audio bitrate to 192 kbps\r\nffmpeg \\\r\n  -loop 1 \\\r\n  -i \"${INPUT_IMAGE}\" \\\r\n  -i \"${INPUT_AUDIO}\" \\\r\n  -t ${VIDEO_DURATION} \\\r\n  -c:v libx264 \\\r\n  -tune stillimage \\\r\n  -pix_fmt yuv420p \\\r\n  -c:a aac \\\r\n  -b:a 192k \\\r\n  \"${OUTPUT_VIDEO}\"\r\n\r\nif [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\r\n    echo \"Video '${OUTPUT_VIDEO}' generated successfu"]
[0.000, "o", "lly.\"\r\nelse\r\n    echo \"Error: Video generation failed.\"\r\n    exit 1\r\nfi\r\n```\r\n\r\n@coder, please proceed with implementing this `render.sh` script.\r\n\r\n"]
